question_text: Based on the thrust equation, compute the net thrust T when ṁ0 = 50 kg/s, ṁf = 1 kg/s, Ve = 550 m/s and V0 = 250 m/s.
Using the general thrust equation T = (ṁ0 + ṁf)Ve − ṁ0V0 + (pe − p0)Ae, compute the pressure term when pe − p0 = 500 Pa and Ae = 0.2 m².
According to the Breguet range equation R = (V∞/(TSFC)) (L/D) ln(W0/W1), compute R when V∞ = 200 m/s, TSFC = 0.5 1/hr, L/D = 15, W0 = 60000 N, W1 = 50000 N.
Given the drag polar CD = CD,0 + KCL², compute CD when CD,0 = 0.02, K = 0.05, and CL = 0.6.
From the equations of motion, compute the parallel force balance T cos ε − D − W sin γ when T = 20000 N, ε = 0°, D = 5000 N, γ = 5°, W = 60000 N.
Using propulsive efficiency formula ηp = 2/(1 + Ve/V0), compute ηp when Ve = 600 m/s and V0 = 200 m/s.
For a turbofan engine with bypass ratio BPR = ṁb/ṁc = 8, core exit velocity Ve = 500 m/s, bypass exit velocity Vb = 300 m/s, and ṁc = 20 kg/s, compute the symbolic total thrust.
Using the turbojet thrust equation T = ṁ0(Ve − V0), compute T when ṁ0 = 45 kg/s, Ve = 900 m/s and V0 = 250 m/s.
From thrust required TR = q∞SCD, compute TR when q∞ = 500 N/m², S = 25 m², and CD = 0.04.
Using TR = (1/2)ρ∞SCD,0 V∞², compute the zero-lift term when ρ∞ = 1.0, S = 30 m², CD,0 = 0.02, V∞ = 70 m/s.
Using the lift equation L = 1/2 ρ∞ V∞² S CL, compute L when ρ∞ = 1.1 kg/m³, V∞ = 90 m/s, S = 25 m², CL = 0.8.
Find the design lift coefficient CL* = sqrt(CD,0 / K) when CD,0 = 0.02 and K = 0.05.
Using the momentum term T = ṁe Ve − ṁ0 V0 with fuel addition ṁe = ṁ0 + ṁf, compute T for ṁ0 = 40, ṁf = 2, Ve = 700, V0 = 250.
Compute endurance E = (1/TSFC)(L/D) ln(W0/W1) for TSFC = 0.6 1/hr, L/D = 12, W0 = 55000 N, W1 = 45000 N.
Using the normal-force balance L + T sin ε − W cos γ = m V²/rc, compute L + T sin ε − W cos γ when T = 15000 N, ε = 3°, W = 50000 N, γ = 0°.
Using ηp = 2/(1 + Ve/V0), find the exhaust velocity ratio Ve/V0 required to achieve ηp = 0.8.
A turbofan has ṁc = 18 kg/s, BPR = 10, Ve = 520 m/s, Vb = 290 m/s. Compute symbolic thrust using T = ṁc(Ve + BPR Vb) − ṁ0 V0.
Using turbojet formula T = ṁ0(Ve − V0), what is thrust when Ve = 1500 ft/s, V0 = 700 ft/s, ṁ0 = 90 lbm/s (use symbolic answer)?
Using TR = q∞ S CD, compute TR symbolically for q∞ = (1/2)ρ∞V∞².
Using maximum L/D formula (L/D)max = sqrt(1/(4 K CD,0)), compute (L/D)max when K = 0.04 and CD,0 = 0.02.
